expect a thing, Mom.

55:24.238 --> 55:26.507
Well, aren't you
a little hothouse flower.

55:28.175 --> 55:30.175
[sighs]
I don't know if you heard,

55:30.177 --> 55:33.014
but I'm training
for the Olympics.

55:34.581 --> 55:36.581
So what do you want?
Money?

55:36.583 --> 55:38.586
God, no. I just...

55:39.521 --> 55:41.019
I just wanted
to see you.

55:41.021 --> 55:42.688
You're a taker.

55:42.690 --> 55:45.791
Every cent I made went to your
skating, and you took it.

55:45.793 --> 55:48.463
- What do you want?
- Jesus.

55:50.764 --> 55:52.999
Well, this was
a stupid fucking idea.

55:53.001 --> 55:54.001
Um...

55:55.869 --> 55:58.970
Was anything I did
ever good enough for you?

55:58.972 --> 56:00.976
You were soft.

56:02.543 --> 56:04.043
At three?

56:04.045 --> 56:05.912
I made you a fighter.

56:05.914 --> 56:07.914
- You never had a chance without me.
- You fucked with my head.

56:07.916 --> 56:10.883
You made me think that I could
skate best when my life was shit.

56:10.885 --> 56:14.787
And now my life is shit... You made
that fucking real... I don't want that.

56:14.789 --> 56:18.861
You would have picked it in a heartbeat.
You should be thanking me, not blaming me.

56:27.601 --> 56:29.537
Did you...
[sighs]

56:30.838 --> 56:32.671
I mean,
when I was a kid,

56:32.673 --> 56:35.978
did you ever love me
or... anything?

56:38.646 --> 56:41.083
You think Sonja Henie's
mother loved her?

56:42.182 --> 56:44.182
Poor fuckin' you.

56:44.184 --> 56:48.724
I didn't stay home making apple brown
betties. No. I made you a champion.

56:49.923 --> 56:51.691
Knowing
you'd hate me for it.

56:51.693 --> 56:53.793
That's the sacrifice
a mother makes.

56:53.795 --> 56:56.361
I wish I'd had a mother
like me instead of nice.

56:56.363 --> 56:57.697
Nice gets you shit.

56:57.699 --> 57:01.670
I didn't like my mother either! So what?
I fuckin' gave you a gift.

57:03.938 --> 57:05.106
You cursed me.

57:12.947 --> 57:14.550
You're a monster.

57:15.215 --> 57:16.817
Spilled milk, baby.

57:21.622 --> 57:23.222
Jeff, are you down here?

57:23.224 --> 57:24.789
Oh, Jeff.

57:24.791 --> 57:28.693
[Jeff] <i>I was pretty surprised
when Tonya called me.</i>

57:28.695 --> 57:30.229
<i>But she said...</i>

57:30.231 --> 57:34.703
[both, simultaneously] I don't think I
can make it to the Olympics without you.

57:37.738 --> 57:39.238
[Jeff]
<i>I admit it.</i>

57:39.240 --> 57:43.242
<i>A part of me still thought that
the sun rose and set with her</i>

57:43.244 --> 57:47.113
<i>and wanted her to look at me
the way that she used to.</i>

57:47.115 --> 57:49.051
<i>I just wanted to hold on.</i>

57:52.019 --> 57:54.720
[Tonya] <i>I figured it was
just for three weeks,</i>

57:54.722 --> 57:57.923
<i>and the second I made the team
I was gonna dump his ass.</i>

57:57.925 --> 57:58.994
<i>But...</i>

58:01.095 --> 58:03.732
before I could think
too much on that,

58:04.999 --> 58:06.331
that... leads...

58:06.333 --> 58:10.204
I mean, it's what you all came for,
folks... the fucking incident.

58:13.041 --> 58:14.240
The incident.

58:14.242 --> 58:15.978
Mmm.

58:18.912 --> 58:20.780
The incident.
[chuckles]

58:20.782 --> 58:22.883
The fucking incident.

58:25.318 --> 58:29.755
Everyone remembers the incident
differently, and that's a fact, um...

58:29.757 --> 58:31.724
- [screaming]
- <i>Some people, honest to God,</i>

58:31.726 --> 58:33.894
<i>remember Tonya
whacking Nancy herself.</i>

58:35.296 --> 58:36.896
[chuckles]

58:36.898 --> 58:41.066
Um... I never talked
about how it went down,

58:41.068 --> 58:42.834
except to the FBI.

58:42.836 --> 58:45.970
<i>The press
got everything wrong.</i>

58:45.972 --> 58:47.539
Excuse me.

58:47.541 --> 58:51.343
I'm with the Clackamas County Sheriff's
Office. I'm gonna need to talk with you.

58:51.345 --> 58:53.311
Oh, goddamn it, Jeff.
What did you do?

58:53.313 --> 58:55.016
I've received
a death threat.

58:55.950 --> 58:57.919
- From Jeff?
- Against you.

58:59.454 --> 59:01.086
What the fuck?

59:01.088 --> 59:03.124
[Jeff] What did
they say, exactly?

59:05.959 --> 59:07.927
Uh, i...
[clears throat]

59:07.929 --> 59:09.829
"If Harding skates today,

59:09.831 --> 59:12.298
she'll get a...
a bullet in the back."

59:12.300 --> 59:14.332
What the fuck?

59:14.334 --> 59:17.035
- How seriously should we take this?
- [Jeff] Right?

59:17.037 --> 59:18.738
Girl skaters
at this level,

59:18.740 --> 59:22.108
they're always messing with each
other with the, um, costumes,

59:22.110 --> 59:23.909
with each other's
skate blades.

59:23.911 --> 59:27.313
- I never knew that.
- Yeah. It's a thing.

59:27.315 --> 59:31.052
Well, the point is, this is a large
venue and we can't protect you.

59:32.353 --> 59:33.885
[hip-hop: scratching]

59:33.887 --> 59:36.521
[woman]
<i>♪ Ooh, baby, baby, yeah ♪</i>

59:36.523 --> 59:40.159
<i>♪ You got me
Got me hung up ♪</i>

59:40.161 --> 59:42.528
In the end, she was
too freaked out to skate.

59:42.530 --> 59:46.231
It screwed with her head
for a long, long time.

59:46.233 --> 59:48.501
And it got me thinking.

59:48.503 --> 59:52.173
Which...
isn't always my strength.

59:54.374 --> 59:58.213
What if I do the same thing to Nancy
Kerrigan, only right before nationals?

59:59.213 --> 01:00:01.113
Yeah. Sort of
even the playing field.

01:00:01.115 --> 01:00:02.247
Right.

01:00:02.249 --> 01:00:05.517
I wouldn't be the first guy
to cheat at figure skating.

01:00:05.519 --> 01:00:08.153
A lot of the judges
are corrupt.

01:00:08.155 --> 01:00:10.189
It's not exactly
prim and proper.

01:00:10.191 --> 01:00:12.260
Someone did it to Tonya,
lest we forget.

01:00:13.161 --> 01:00:15.394
It's... my way of...

01:00:15.396 --> 01:00:17.829
saying "I love you."

01:00:17.831 --> 01:00:20.301
Interested. Go on.

01:00:21.501 --> 01:00:23.369
No, that's it.

01:00:23.371 --> 01:00:27.405
I figure I'm gonna mail some
letters to screw with her head.

01:00:27.407 --> 01:00:29.307
Whoa.

01:00:29.309 --> 01:00:31.746
You f-in' greenhorn.

01:00:32.546 --> 01:00:34.782
You cannot mail letters
from here.

01:00:36.016 --> 01:00:38.352
- It'll be postmarked from Portland.
- No.

01:00:40.021 --> 01:00:42.320
What we do, see, is...
[clears throat]

01:00:42.322 --> 01:00:44.289
we send somebody
out there.

01:00:44.291 --> 01:00:47.193
We fly 'em out there, or maybe to
Massachusetts, where she's from.

01:00:47.195 --> 01:00:48.494
Yeah.

01:00:48.496 --> 01:00:51.564
Takes the suspicion
off of us, see?

01:00:51.566 --> 01:00:52.801
Right.

01:00:53.601 --> 01:00:55.103
I know a guy.

01:00:56.470 --> 01:00:59.070
Shouldn't even be
saying his name.

01:00:59.072 --> 01:01:00.405
Derrick.

01:01:00.407 --> 01:01:03.242
All in, you're probably
looking at a thousand bucks,

01:01:03.244 --> 01:01:06.148
but you really ought to
let me handle everything.

01:01:11.985 --> 01:01:14.320
[pop song playing on radio]
<i>♪ Gloria ♪</i>

01:01:14.322 --> 01:01:17.990
<i>♪ You're always on the run now ♪</i>

01:01:17.992 --> 01:01:21.526
- <i>♪ Runnin' after somebody ♪</i>
- ♪ Somebody ♪

01:01:21.528 --> 01:01:25.396
- <i>♪ You've gotta get him somehow ♪</i>
- [humming]

01:01:25.398 --> 01:01:29.068
[singing along] <i>♪ I think
You've got to slow down ♪</i>

01:01:29.070 --> 01:01:31.102
<i>♪ Before you start to blow it ♪</i>

01:01:31.104 --> 01:01:34.106
<i>- ♪ Dah dah dah ♪
- ♪ I think you're headed For a break... ♪</i>

01:01:34.108 --> 01:01:36.909
- [Jeff] <i>Us being great spies and all,</i>
- [tape rewinding]

01:01:36.911 --> 01:01:41.347
<i>we call up a friend who leaves a
message where Kerrigan trains...</i>

01:01:41.349 --> 01:01:44.215
For fuck sake. Jeff,
just call her back.

01:01:44.217 --> 01:01:48.186
<i>Only our machine is so old we
can't completely understand it.</i>

01:01:48.188 --> 01:01:50.990
She just said Nancy
Kerrigan trains at...

01:01:50.992 --> 01:01:52.557
- [woman] <i>Kerrigan trains...</i>
- [man] <i>At Tuna Can Arena.</i>

01:01:52.559 --> 01:01:55.260
Nancy Kerrigan trains at Tuna Can Arena.
She just said that.

01:01:55.262 --> 01:01:57.364
Well, who's gonna name
an arena "Tuna Can"?

01:01:58.932 --> 01:02:01.969
Fishermen. Everyone's
fishermen in Massachusetts.

01:02:04.204 --> 01:02:06.106
Just fucking
call her back and ask.

01:02:09.677 --> 01:02:11.644
[ringing]

01:02:11.646 --> 01:02:13.979
Hi, Vera.
It's Tonya again.

01:02:13.981 --> 01:02:16.581
Mm-hmm. Our machine's
a piece of crap.

01:02:16.583 --> 01:02:19.584
Could you just tell me where
Nancy Kerrigan trains again?

01:02:19.586 --> 01:02:23.521
- [Vera] <i>Oh, sure.</i>
- Yeah, I had a stupid bet with Jeff.

01:02:23.523 --> 01:02:25.691
Mm-hmm.
Spell that for me, hon.

01:02:25.693 --> 01:02:26.995
Uh-huh.

01:02:28.095 --> 01:02:29.994
- And what time?
- <i>5:45.</i>

01:02:29.996 --> 01:02:32.631
- Got it. Thanks, Vera.
- [Vera] <i>No problem.</i>

01:02:32.633 --> 01:02:34.135
Yeah. See you later.

01:02:35.202 --> 01:02:37.936
It's that fuckin' easy.
Tony Kent.

01:02:37.938 --> 01:02:39.671
Thank you. Tony Kent.

01:02:39.673 --> 01:02:42.240
- Tony Kent Arena.
- Not Tuna Can.

01:02:42.242 --> 01:02:45.913
Tony Kent Arena.
It's the same fucking thing.

01:02:46.546 --> 01:02:48.180
Dinner's ready.

01:02:48.182 --> 01:02:52.418
It's bullshit. I mean, the FBI
found this piece of paper

01:02:52.420 --> 01:02:54.619
in some random Dumpster,

01:02:54.621 --> 01:03:00.559
supposedly in my handwriting, with Nancy's
training schedule or something on it.

01:03:00.561 --> 01:03:05.030
It was the arena Nancy skated at
and her training times.

01:03:05.032 --> 01:03:06.497
What do you need
training times for

01:03:06.499 --> 01:03:09.133
if all you're doing
is mailing letters, right?

01:03:09.135 --> 01:03:12.704
Jeff Gillooly can change his story all
he wants to make himself feel better,

01:03:12.706 --> 01:03:15.441
but he confessed to the FBI.

01:03:15.443 --> 01:03:16.476
Guilty.

01:03:16.478 --> 01:03:20.546
I told the FBI that Tonya
was in on planning it,

01:03:20.548 --> 01:03:22.383
<i>which she was.</i>

01:03:23.351 --> 01:03:27.251
<i>But the plan was
to mail some letters.</i>

01:03:27.253 --> 01:03:29.188
Tonya didn't know
about the assault,

01:03:29.190 --> 01:03:31.492
because there was never
supposed to be an assault.

01:03:34.528 --> 01:03:35.528
Just letters.

01:03:39.367 --> 01:03:40.367
[door closes]

01:03:51.345 --> 01:03:53.415
[Jeff] I gave Shawn
a thousand bucks.

01:03:57.050 --> 01:03:58.420
Nothing happens.

01:04:00.086 --> 01:04:02.120
Gonna need to come up
with more money.

01:04:02.122 --> 01:04:05.090
Do I have "stupid"
written across my head?

01:04:05.092 --> 01:04:09.160
All they had to do was mail letters
someplace. I'm not giving them more money.

01:04:09.162 --> 01:04:11.363
But these are two
of my top operatives.

01:04:11.365 --> 01:04:13.432
Derrick needs
expense money...

01:04:13.434 --> 01:04:17.035
